MatlabReplica/
 |
 | matlab_replica/ (project source code)
    | matlab_replica_backend/ (C Backend)
        | src/
            | mpMatrix.c ------------------ (implements matrix generation and manipulation functionalities)
            | mpMath.c -------------------- (implements basic and classic math functionalities)
            | mpMemory.c ------------------ (implements memory management functionalities)
            | mpAvx.c --------------------- (implements low-level functions that call avx instructions with 
                                      \----  inline asm for matrix manipulation)
        | build/
            | libMatlabReplica.dll
        | include/
            | matlabReplica.h ------------- (Wrapper around all library header files)
            | mpMatrix.h ------------------ (matrix generation and manipulation function and data declarations)
            | mpMath.h -------------------- (basic and classic math function declarations)
            | mpMemory.h ------------------ (internal memory management function declarations)
            | mpAvx.h
        | test/
            | test.c ---------------------- (a simple executable for quick testing the library)
    | __init__.py ------------------------- (module initializer)  
    | abc.py      ------------------------- (Base classes and Abstraction layers)
        | Classes |
        | LowLevelInterface --------------- (implements low-level connection interfaces between python and other libraries)
        | ... (TBD)
    | overrides.py ------------------------ (a module that provides python implementation overrides)
        | BuiltinOverrides ---------------- (replaces python builtin data-types with corresponding ones in matlab-replica)
        | InterpreterOverride ------------- (provides a method of changing interpreter behaviour and adding new syntax)
    | matrix.py --------------------------- (Matrix base interface implementations)
        | MetaMatrix ---------------------- (metaclass for re-implementing matrix class functionalities)
        | Matrix -------------------------- (Super matrix class)
    | classicmath.py ---------------------- (Classic math functions that work on numbers)
 | setup.py ------------------------------- (Module setup script, for installation with pip)
 | pyproject.toml ------------------------- (same as above for newer versions of python)
 | venv/ ---------------------------------- (project virtual environment directory)
 
